好的补充。</p><p><em>在 Twitter 上</em><em>关注</em><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/EngadgetDeals"><em>@EngadgetDeals</em></a>并<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://subscription.yahoo.net/Newsletter/Preference/sub?b=engadgetdeals&amp;src"><em>订阅 Engadget Deals 时事通讯，</em></a><em>了解最新的科技交易和购买建议。</em></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/googles-pixel-watch-2-falls-to-a-new-low-of-300-102522276.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/googles-pixel-watch-2-falls-to-a-new-low-of-300-102522276.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 1e80bda6-51a3-49b7-b1e7-68db65695136</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 04 Dec 2023 10:25:22 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701684396</ingested><modified> 2023-12-04T10:06:40+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2F7034de50-9286-11ee-957f-4ab05254b9fc&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=1cc5d2ac44f737f4fe58a5cab1fb670097ad8417" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2F7034de50-9286-11ee-957f-4ab05254b9fc&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=3c172b8a59edd62117ae8eb346c7af16f5e130df" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Google's Pixel Watch 2 falls to a new low of $300]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Google's Pixel Watch 2 falls to a new low of $300]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Spotify laying off 17 percent of employees across the company]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Spotify 首席执行官丹尼尔·埃克 (Daniel Ek) 在<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://newsroom.spotify.com/2023-12-04/an-update-on-december-2023-organizational-changes/">公司新闻稿</a>中宣布，节前令人震惊的是，Spotify 将在公司范围内裁员 17%。此次削减是由于埃克所说的“未来的挑战”，他选择立即进行削减，而不是随着时间的推移进行较小的削减。他补充说，受影响的员工将于今天晚些时候收到通知。</p><p>埃克写道：“我意识到，对于许多人来说，考虑到最近积极的盈利报告和我们的业绩，这种规模的缩减会让人感到惊讶。” “我们讨论了在 2024 年和 2025 年期间进行较小规模的削减。然而，考虑到我们的财务目标状态与当前运营成本之间的差距，我认为采取实质性行动来调整我们的成本是实现我们目标的最佳选择。虽然我我确信这对我们公司来说是正确的行动，我也理解这对我们的团队来说将是极其痛苦的。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Ek 继续指出，由于资本成本较低，该公司在 2020 年和 2021 年大幅扩张。他表示：“这些投资总体上是有效的，有助于 Spotify 产量的增加以及该平台去年的强劲增长。”尽管去年进行了裁员——该公司在 2023 年初解雇了<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-will-lay-off-6-percent-of-employees-130337498.html">6% 的员工</a>， <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-is-laying-off-200-employees-from-its-podcast-division-134749721.html">5 月份又解雇了 2%</a> ——“我们的成本结构仍然太大了，”埃克说。</p><p>在这几轮裁员之后，Spotify 拥有约 9,000 名员工，因此最新的裁员将导致约 1,500 名员工失业（截至 2022 年，其中 4,300 名员工在美国）。为了减轻打击，埃克表示 Spotify 将支付平均 5 个月的遣散费，支付这段时间内的医疗费用，并提供移民/职业支持。</p><p> Ek 表示，对于公司的下一阶段，“精益不仅是一种选择，而且是必要的。”上个月，Spotify 宣布了改进的版税模式，旨在为“在职艺术家”提供更大的提成，同时减少欺诈性流媒体。</p><p> Spotify 自推出以来一直持续增长，目前每月活跃用户数为 5.74 亿，比去年同期增长 26%。该公司一直难以盈利，但<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://newsroom.spotify.com/2023-10-24/spotify-reports-third-quarter-2023-earnings/#:~:text=Total%20Revenue%20grew%2011%25%20Y,32%20million%20for%20the%20quarter.">上个季度</a>是一个罕见的例外。埃克承诺“在未来几天和几周内”提供更多有关这些变化意味着什么的信息，但对于在假期前突然发现自己失业的员工来说，所有这些都将是冰冷的安慰。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/spotify-laying-off-17-percent-of-employees-across-the-company-081521784.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/spotify-laying-off-17-percent-of-employees-across-the-company-081521784.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> f501e293-1aae-4699-862e-acc28ad8f87b</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 04 Dec 2023 08:15:21 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701677929</ingested><modified> 2023-12-04T08:18:54+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Finance]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="787" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-01%2F3c0e2650-a343-11ed-bdf9-267e38e37f9e&amp;resize=1400%2C787&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=eaaf90b44740eb1a3041c273abae87b1f210405f" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="787" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-01%2F3c0e2650-a343-11ed-bdf9-267e38e37f9e&amp;resize=1400%2C787&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=21f244f1492e850831704d2fd1ab727a222e6bb5" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[VIEW press via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[NEW YORK, NEW YORK - JANUARY 23: People are seen inside the Spotify headquarters building in Lower Manhattan on January 23, 2023 in New York City. Spotify announced Monday they will be cutting 6% of its global workforce. (Photo by Eduardo MunozAlvarez/VIEWpress via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Spotify To Cut 6 Percent Of Its Global Workforce]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meta's latest AI suite makes speech translation more seamless and expressive]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>早在 8 月份，Meta 就推出了其多模式 AI 翻译模型<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-new-multimodal-translator-uses-a-single-model-to-speak-100-languages-133040214.html">SeamlessM4T</a> ，该模型支持近 100 种文本语言和 36 种语音语言。通过更新的“v2”架构，这家科技巨头现在正在<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://ai.meta.com/research/seamless-communication/">扩展</a>该工具，以使对话翻译更加自发和富有表现力——后者是跨语言真实对话的缺失关键。</p><p>这两个新功能中的第一个是“SeamlessExpressive”，正如您从名称中可以看出的那样，它将您的表情移植到翻译的语音中。这些包括你的音调、音量、情绪基调（兴奋、悲伤或耳语）、语速和停顿。考虑到迄今为止，翻译后的演讲听起来总是机械的，这一突破可能会改变游戏规则——无论是在我们的日常生活中，还是在内容制作中。支持的语言包括英语、西班牙语、德语、法语、意大利语和中文，但在撰写本文时<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://seamless.metademolab.com/expressive/">演示页面</a>缺少意大利语和中文。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>第二个功能是“无缝流媒体”，它可以在讲话者仍在讲话时开始翻译语音，从而使其他人能够更快地听到翻译。虽然仍然有不到两秒的短暂延迟，但至少您不必等到有人说完一句话。根据 Meta 的说法，这里的挑战是不同的语言有不同的句子结构，因此它必须开发一种专门研究部分音频输入的算法，以便决定是否有足够的上下文来开始生成翻译输出，或者是否继续收听。</p><p> Meta 在这一“无缝通信”套件上的最新开发似乎令人印象深刻——比<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-google-pixel-folds-dual-screen-interpreter-begins-rolling-out-170003067.html">谷歌</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-teases-its-own-ai-based-real-time-phone-call-translation-053818106.html">三星等</a>公司提供的移动解释器工具更令人印象深刻。目前还没有关于公众何时能够使用这些新功能的消息，但我已经可以想象有一天 Meta 将它们融入到其<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ray-ban-meta-hands-on-techy-sunglasses-you-might-actually-want-to-wear-180852514.html">智能眼镜</a>中，使它们比以往任何时候都更加实用。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/metas-latest-ai-suite-makes-speech-translation-more-seamless-and-expressive-060043686.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/metas-latest-ai-suite-makes-speech-translation-more-seamless-and-expressive-060043686.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> bcee6c01-747c-4841-b5c2-09699d12cd25</guid><dc:creator>理查德·赖</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 04 Dec 2023 03:50:14 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701662052</ingested><modified> 2023-12-04T03:54:14+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Richard Lai]]></category><media:content height="875" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fdbb8b770-9257-11ee-adcf-8bb60d3b998b&amp;resize=1400%2C875&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=b9fcc327a576ec3254f2577147c3223bfc4d22af" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="875" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fdbb8b770-9257-11ee-adcf-8bb60d3b998b&amp;resize=1400%2C875&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;si