shing the launch of its Gemini AI to 2024]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>据<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:1;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.theinformation.com/articles/google-postpones-big-ai-launch-as-openai-zooms-ahead?rc=whf0fd" data-original-link="https://www.theinformation.com/articles/google-postpones-big-ai-launch-as-openai-zooms-ahead?rc=whf0fd"><em>The Information 报道，</em></a>谷歌取消了原定于下周举行的 Gemini 发布会，现在计划于 1 月份推出其 GPT-4 竞争对手。该公司在 I/O 2023 上嘲笑<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:2;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://blog.google/technology/ai/google-io-2023-keynote-sundar-pichai/#ai-responsibility" data-original-link="https://blog.google/technology/ai/google-io-2023-keynote-sundar-pichai/#ai-responsibility">Gemini</a> ，并在培训初期将其宣传为具有“令人印象深刻的多模式功能”的基础模型。</p><p>谷歌最初计划在今年年底前在假期期间推出，但谷歌并未公开宣布这一消息，但消息人士告诉<em>The Information</em> ，Gemini 正在努力应对非英语查询，促使首席执行官桑达尔·皮查伊 (Sundar Pichai) 推迟了这一计划。它的释放。 Gemini 旨在能够处理广泛的应用程序，结合图像和文本等不同类型的数据来执行更高级的任务。 5 月，谷歌表示，“一旦经过微调和严格的安全测试，Gemini 将提供各种尺寸和功能。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Gemini 预计还将改进谷歌现有的人工智能和人工智能增强产品，例如 Bard、Google Assistant 和 Search。但是，考虑到这次发布的重要性以及竞争对手 OpenAI 在该领域已经占据的主导地位，谷歌似乎不会冒险将 Gemini 赶出大门。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/google-is-reportedly-pushing-the-launch-of-its-gemini-ai-to-2024-173444507.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/google-is-reportedly-pushing-the-launch-of-its-gemini-ai-to-2024-173444507.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ce3d1384-4f44-4742-93a7-dddf51bbb155</guid><dc:creator>夏安·麦克唐纳</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Sun, 03 Dec 2023 17:34:44 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701625989</ingested><modified> 2023-12-03T17:53:11+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Cheyenne MacDonald]]></category><media:content height="953" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-images%2F2019-11%2Fde23acd0-0b84-11ea-9b76-9559e1097c73&amp;resize=1400%2C953&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=b62fab54b336291bb07cf48593560667b8ea2651" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="953" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-images%2F2019-11%2Fde23acd0-0b84-11ea-9b76-9559e1097c73&amp;resize=1400%2C953&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=118008c8750e0ae8e8925d93b1aa7c776ef8a7bf" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Reuters Staff / Reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A sign is pictured outs a Google offcie near the company's headquarters in Mountain View, California, U.S., May 8, 2019.  Photo taken May 8, 2019.  REUTERS/Dave Paresh]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ALPHABET-GOOGLE/DEVELOPERS]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[23andMe hackers accessed ancestry information on millions of customers using a feature that matches relatives]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:1;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.sec.gov/ix?doc=/Archives/edgar/data/1804591/000119312523287449/d242666d8ka.htm" data-original-link="https://www.sec.gov/ix?doc=/Archives/edgar/data/1804591/000119312523287449/d242666d8ka.htm">美国证券交易委员会 (SEC) 的一份文件</a>披露了今年秋季早些时候披露的<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:2;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/23andme-user-data-breached-in-credential-stuffing-attack-231757254.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/23andme-user-data-breached-in-credential-stuffing-attack-231757254.html">影响 23andMe 用户的数据泄露</a>的更多细节。 <a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:3;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://techcrunch.com/2023/12/01/23andme-says-hackers-accessed-significant-number-of-files-about-users-ancestry/" data-original-link="https://techcrunch.com/2023/12/01/23andme-says-hackers-accessed-significant-number-of-files-about-users-ancestry/"><em>TechCrunch</em></a>指出，该公司表示，调查发现黑客能够访问其用户群中约 0.1% 的账户，即 1400 万客户中的约 14,000 名。最重要的是，攻击者能够利用 23andMe 的选择加入 DNA 亲属 (DNAR) 功能（该功能将用户与其遗传亲属进行匹配）来访问数百万其他用户的信息。 23andMe 发言人告诉 Engadget，黑客通过这种方式获取了大约 550 万客户的 DNAR 档案，以及 140 万 DNA 相关参与者的家谱档案信息。</p><p> DNAR 配置文件包含敏感详细信息，包括自我报告的信息，如显示名称和位置，以及 DNA 亲属匹配的共享 DNA 百分比、姓氏、预测关系和血统报告。家谱配置文件包含显示名称和关系标签，以及用户可以选择添加的其他信息，包括出生年份和位置。当十月份泄露事件首次被揭露时，该公司表示，其调查“发现没有基因检测结果被泄露”。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>根据新提交的文件，这些数据“通常包括血统信息，对于这些帐户的子集，还包括基于用户基因的健康相关信息。”所有这些都是通过凭证填充攻击获得的，其中黑客使用来自其他先前受感染的网站的登录信息来访问这些用户在其他网站上的帐户。文件称，在此过程中，“威胁行为者还访问了大量包含其他用户祖先个人资料信息的文件，这些用户在选择加入 23andMe 的 DNA 亲属功能时选择共享这些文件，并在网上发布了某些信息。”</p><p>发现漏洞后， <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://blog.23andme.com/articles/addressing-data-security-concerns">23andMe</a>指示受影响的用户更改密码，随后为其所有客户推出了双因素身份验证。在周五的另一次更新中，23andMe 表示已完成调查并通知所有受影响的人。该公司还在文件中写道，它“相信威胁行为者的活动已得到控制”，并正在努力删除公开发布的信息。</p><p><strong>更新，美国东部时间 2023 年 12 月 2 日晚上 7:03：本文已更新，包含 23andMe 发言人提供的有关泄露范围和受影响的 DNA 相关参与者数量的信息。</strong></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/23andme-hackers-accessed-ancestry-information-from-thousands-of-customers-and-their-dna-relatives-205758731.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/23andme-hackers-accessed-ancestry-information-from-thousands-of-customers-and-their-dna-relatives-205758731.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 7effecd1-4e72-418c-8d08-25031cfb3e1c</guid><dc:creator>夏安·麦克唐纳</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Sat, 02 Dec 2023 20:57:58 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701561977</ingested><modified> 2023-12-03T00:06:20+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Cheyenne MacDonald]]></category><media:content height="945" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2021-09%2Fe353af40-1bac-11ec-bb8c-b9f37feac611&amp;resize=1400%2C945&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=1b59e8fd90d8bbbf754f1baec6cc012cebc15daa" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="945" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2021-09%2Fe353af40-1bac-11ec-bb8c-b9f37feac611&amp;resize=1400%2C945&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=2ebd9f01f1e1ac02f8c58fea9d843ef84fecc3bb" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[SOPA Images via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[UKRAINE - 2021/06/17: In this photo illustration, 23andMe logo of a biotechnology company is seen on a smartphone and a pc screen in the background. (Photo Illustration by Pavlo Gonchar/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[In this photo illustration, 23andMe logo of a biotechnology...]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Amazon is swallowing its pride to ensure its internet satellites get to orbit on time]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>亚马逊周五<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:1;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/innovation-at-amazon/amazon-project-kuiper-spacex-launch" data-original-link="https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/innovation-at-amazon/amazon-project-kuiper-spacex-launch"><ins>宣布</ins></a>与 SpaceX 签署合同，将于 2025 年向近地轨道批量交付 Project Kuiper 卫星<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:2;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/starlinks-satellite-cell-service-is-set-to-launch-in-2024-but-only-for-sms-215036124.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/starlinks-satellite-cell-service-is-set-to-launch-in-2024-but-only-for-sms-215036124.html"><ins>。SpaceX 无疑是亚马逊进军卫星互联网领域的最大竞争对手</ins></a>，目前已经拥有超过 4000 颗 Starlink 星座正在运行的卫星。它也是杰夫·贝佐斯创立的航空航天公司蓝色起源的竞争对手，该公司正在开发自己的火箭。但在发射方面，SpaceX 的猎鹰 9 号火箭的速度和可靠性是无与伦比的。</p><p>亚马逊在博客文章中表示，与 SpaceX 签订的合同涉及三次猎鹰 9 号发射。它们预计将于 2025 年中期升空。亚马逊计划在明年底之前启动其 Project Kuiper 卫星互联网服务的客户试点，并将很快开始部署支持该服务的机队。它<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:3;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazons-first-internet-satellite-launch-was-a-success-202130763.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/amazons-first-internet-satellite-launch-was-a-success-202130763.html"><ins>于十月份发射了前两颗原型卫星</ins></a>。该公司已经与联合发射联盟 (ULA) 的火神火箭、阿丽亚娜航天公司的阿丽亚娜 6 号火箭和蓝色起源的新格伦火箭达成了即将发射的协议，所有这些火箭都受到了开发延迟的影响，可能会或可能不会在今年和明年之间进行首次飞行。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>亚马逊在声明中表示，“与 SpaceX 的额外发射提供了更多的能力来支持我们的部署计划。”该公司表示，其<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:4;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/innovation-at-amazon/what-is-amazon-project-kuiper" data-original-link="https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/innovation-at-amazon/what-is-amazon-project-kuiper"><ins>柯伊伯星座项目</ins></a>将由 3,236 颗卫星组成，其中至少一半必须在 2026 年夏季之前投入运行，以符合 FCC 许可的要求。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/amazon-is-swallowing-its-pride-to-ensure-its-internet-satellites-get-to-orbit-on-time-222906412.html ?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/amazon-is-swallowing-its-pride-to-ensure-its-internet-satellites-get-to-orbit-on-time-222906412.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 9e89110c-16a8-46d3-8ed5-8f1bda23e2cc</guid><dc:creator>夏安·麦克唐纳</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Sat, 02 Dec 2023 22:29:06 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701556147</ingested><modified> 2023-12-02T22:29:11+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Cheyenne MacDonald]]></category><media:content height="720" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-11%2Fffe91f60-9160-11ee-bcbe-a9ba6b393788&amp;resize=1400%2C720&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=634153e6a4ae420b924788117e3ac3a6ae05c232" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="720" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-11%2Fffe91f60-9160-11ee-bcbe-a9ba6b393788&amp;resize=1400%2C720&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=4c04068f4b4a5f94d1294e7735d4e29f83e8be74" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Steve Nesius / reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[SpaceX launches a Falcon 9 rocket carrying a pair of television broadcasting satellites for Intelsat from launch pad 40 at Cape Canaveral, Florida, U.S. November 12, 2022. REUTERS/Steve Nesius]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[SPACE-EXPLORATION/SPACEX]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Amazon just dropped the first teaser trailer for its Fallout series]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>亚马逊发布了<em>《辐射》的首部官方预告片，</em>这是其即将推出的基于畅销视频游戏的真人系列电影。这段视频让我们了解了亚马逊对后世界末日荒原的看法，以及<em>黄衫队</em>演员埃拉·珀内尔 (Ella Purnell) 从 33 号避难所出现，第一次见到它。该剧以核战争将地球夷为废墟 200 年后的洛杉矶为背景。 </p><div id="4bfc3f64c1fb49a5a6c3855ac52cfcb3"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/i8qRasXF2pY?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen scrolling="no" data-embed-domain="www.youtube.com"></iframe></div><p>预告片在<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:1;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazons-new-fallout-series-will-reveal-the-origins-of-vault-boy-221607044.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/amazons-new-fallout-series-will-reveal-the-origins-of-vault-boy-221607044.html">亚马逊发布剧照</a>几天后发布，现在更深入地展示了角色以及他们将在荒野中遇到的恐怖。到目前为止，这似乎是一个有希望的迹象，表明该系列将如何处理其深受喜爱的源材料。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>与珀内尔一起主演的<em>《辐射》</em>还包括沃尔顿·戈金斯（ <em>《八恶人</em>》）饰演一名突围的食尸鬼，亚伦·莫顿（《<em>解放</em>》）饰演钢铁兄弟会成员，凯尔·麦克拉克伦（《<em>双峰</em>》）饰演金库监督。还有<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/entertainment/fallout-series-dog-character-cx404">一只名为 CX404 的狗</a>，我们在视频和营销材料中看到它带着一只断手。 <em>《辐射》</em>将于明年 4 月 12 日在 Prime Video 上上映。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/amazon-just-dropped-the-first-teaser-trailer-for-its-fallout-series-182055521.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/amazon-just-dropped-the-first-teaser-trailer-for-its-fallout-series-182055521.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 79761fbe-42e8-4ac2-b304-597df43923c3</guid><dc:creator>夏安·麦克唐纳</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Sat, 02 Dec 2023 18:20:55 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701541256</ingested><modified> 2023-12-02T18:21:04+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Cheyenne MacDonald]]></category><media:content height="788" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fb6a376b0-913e-11ee-87fb-fe950c89f3c0&amp;resize=1400%2C788&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=63d796c0bcc2113a2e9cfa280f98907756b834cc" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="788" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fb6a376b0-913e-11ee-87fb-fe950c89f3c0&amp;resize=1400%2C788&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=4bc2210874ef529917f3f8c91d1b73e2ceeb27f1" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Amazon]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A still from Amazon's Fallout series]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Fallout Amazon]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Universal Audio is giving away Volt 2 audio interfaces with Spark subscriptions]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>许多公司为了庆祝节日而赠送免费插件，但 Universal Audio 更进一步。这家音频巨头将通过购买其 Spark 插件平台的年度订阅<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://spark.uaudio.com/?">免费赠送 Volt 2 硬件接口</a>。这些接口的价格通常为 170 美元，因此对于初学者来说这是一笔非常划算的交易，因为硬件加上 Spark 软件几乎已经满足了您所需的一切。</p><p><core-commerce id="c0c94e7951cd4646b8a16aa6268f4d1a" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Spark 订阅也在假期期间打折，价格为 150 美元，而不是 240 美元，尽管这个价格点相当常见。最终结果？你支付 150 美元，就可以使用该服务上的每个可用插件一年，再加上 Volt 2。不错。该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/universal-audio-spark-plugin-subscription-windows-10-11-190040415.html">基于订阅的 Spark 平台</a>允许访问<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://help.uaudio.com/hc/en-us/articles/5230697410836-Which-UAD-plug-ins-are-available-natively-and-in-UAD-Spark-">数十种流行的 UAD 插件，</a>从 1176 等标志性压缩器到该公司 Minimoog 复制品等虚拟乐器。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>至于 Volt 2，这款小型音频接口的前端有一对 TRS / XLR 输入以及相关的增益控制旋钮。有一个用于电容麦克风的幻象电源按钮和一个专有的复古模式，可通过简单的电子管前置放大器模拟运行信号。这些接口通过 USB-C 供电，但配有 5V 插孔，供您插入 iPad 或其他移动设备时使用。</p><p>在我们的官方评测中， <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/universal-audio-volt-2-volt-276-review-audio-interface-home-studio-170050385.html">我们赞扬了 Volt 2 音频接口</a>的最低本底噪声、简单的控制和低延迟，尤其是在 Windows 机器上。最大的缺点是价格，这通常是 UAD 产品的情况。现在这个促销活动的价格降到了 0 美元，这种担忧已经消失了。</p><p>这并不是 UAD 第一次利用假期赠送免费硬件。该公司过去常常通过购买价格较高的硬件产品（例如多通道 4-710d 前置放大器和压缩器）来提供免费的卫星 DSP 加速器来运行其插件。</p><p><em>在 Twitter 上</em><em>关注</em><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/EngadgetDeals"><em>@EngadgetDeals</em></a>并<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://subscription.yahoo.net/Newsletter/Preference/sub?b=engadgetdeals&amp;src"><em>订阅 Engadget Deals 时事通讯，</em></a><em>了解最新的科技交易和购买建议。</em></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/universal-audio-is-giving-away-volt-2-audio-interfaces-with-spark-subscriptions-182131900.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/universal-audio-is-giving-away-volt-2-audio-interfaces-with-spark-subscriptions-182131900.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 6a6f3e25-c9a1-4e1c-b905-cde3580fd402</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 28 Nov 2023 18:21:31 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701540160</ingested><modified> 2023-12-02T18:02:53+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="786" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-11%2F1cffa7a0-8e18-11ee-bff3-45ec2d6c58e9&amp;resize=1400%2C786&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=554be6444c553597cabfc2877532c21f8f66f41b" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="786" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-11%2F1cffa7a0-8e18-11ee-bff3-45ec2d6c58e9&amp;resize=1400%2C786&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=0fb66737c4845843b06308fa86b11e019f8db4fd" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Terrence O'Brien / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[An image of an audio interface on a desk.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Volt 2]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[OpenAI’s GPT Store won’t be released until 2024]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>根据<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:1;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/12/1/23984497/openai-gpt-store-delayed-ai-gpt" data-original-link="https://www.theverge.com/2023/12/1/23984497/openai-gpt-store-delayed-ai-gpt"><em>The Verge</em></a>看到的一封电子邮件，OpenAI 正在将 GPT Store 的推出时间推迟到 2024 年初。该公司于 11 月初在其首次开发者大会上<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:2;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/gpts-are-the-single-application-mini-chatgpt-models-that-anyone-can-create-203311858.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/gpts-are-the-single-application-mini-chatgpt-models-that-anyone-can-create-203311858.html">推出了 GPT Builder 工具</a>，为订阅者提供了一种创建自己的定制 AI 机器人的简单方法。当时，OpenAI还表示将很快发布GPT Store，供用户列出他们的GPT并可能从中赚钱。它最初定于 11 月推出。但是，随着<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:3;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-joins-openai-board-as-sam-altman-returns-as-ceo-023844090.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-joins-openai-board-as-sam-altman-returns-as-ceo-023844090.html">OpenAI 首席执行官萨姆·奥尔特曼 (Sam Altman) 出人意料地被罢免，该公司后来复职，</a>这个月的业绩并没有按计划进行。</p><p> “就下一步而言，我们现在计划明年初推出 GPT 商店，”OpenAI 在周五发给 GPT Builder 用户的电子邮件中表示。 “虽然我们原计划本月发布它，但有些事情让我们出乎意料地忙碌！”该电子邮件还指出，该公司一直在根据用户的反馈对 GPT 进行改进，并表示 ChatGPT 的一些更新正在进行中。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>在经历了过去几周的动荡之后，OpenAI 一直在重组其领导层。该公司周三确认 Altman 重新担任首席执行官，米拉·穆拉蒂 (Mira Murati) 担任首席技术官，格雷格·布罗克曼 (Greg Brockman) 担任总裁。它还宣布组建新的初始董事会，其中<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:4;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-joins-openai-board-as-sam-altman-returns-as-ceo-023844090.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-joins-openai-board-as-sam-altman-returns-as-ceo-023844090.html">包括其最大投资者微软的代表</a>，作为无投票权的观察员。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/openais-gpt-store-wont-be-released-until-2024-162113991.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/openais-gpt-store-wont-be-released-until-2024-162113991.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 6211fa37-d996-4004-bd28-29f3c654c89e</guid><dc:creator>夏安·麦克唐纳</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Sat, 02 Dec 2023 16:21:13 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1701535043</ingested><modified> 2023-12-02T16:37:32+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Finance]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Cheyenne MacDonald]]></category><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-02%2F0c4aeb20-b43b-11ed-9ffb-e7168c7d91f7&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=b1f1c0707514b45a959eedf65afeb45535cb74ed" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-02%2F0c4aeb20-b43b-11ed-9ffb-e